This Sci-Fi Drama was exactly as I remembered it, the reason I gave a four was because of the packaging. The manufacturing folks could have really just gone with a simpler system and had better protection for the disc. In 4 of the 5 seasons I purchased, there were discs flopping around inside the box. Luckly there wasn't any damage.
I am now on season  two. It is as I remember. Can't wait to get through the rest of the seasons.

So far (I am on Disk 1) the second episode is in Fullscreen while the rest are Widescreen; some kind of error I guess. Anyway, the entire series is well worth watching if you have time. Some say S1 is the best which may be true but I like them all. A bit expensive but worth it if you're a Sci-Fi Fan.

While the series may not be EXCELLENT start to finish, there are certainly enough great episodes coupled with the merely good to make it worth watching.

Even without already knowing that this series was canceled, you do get a feeling that the end was near. The humans are starting to shake off their dependence on the Taelons and the Taelons are themselves in serious trouble. As always, many of the better shows end up being axed and the crappy ones seem to go on forever. Sad that, unlike the original Star Trek, EFC did not continue on in syndication. There is one bad thing. The packaging of the discs is a very poor design. The discs ore overlaying each other and the case does not hold them secure. As a result, the DVDs fall out of the case and slide around each other, thus risking the chance of being scratched. Not sure who the Einstein was that designed this case, but they should have been kicked in the backside for this poor desin. If you are thinking of getting season five, as well, be advised the DVDs are packaged in the same style.
Another great series from Gene Rodenberry. I decided to purchase all the season sets because I like the creator and the storyline.
An excellent series. Wish it would've run longer. It was kind of like "V" meets "Red Dawn".  If you liked those two shows you'll love this series.
I loved this series.  I was able to watch all the episodes from the beginning.  I would highly recommend it.

For those of you who enjoy Science Fiction, you'll see the dark side of the Taelon companions.  One might consider the series flawed when a so called "advanced race" suffers the same lust for power, but the series is enjoyable.

Finally whole series released - Ive Waitng along time for this series to come out on DVD or Blu Ray.

Although none of the actors were familiar to me, they were superb.  The series concept was well-thought out and the sets and special effects were great.  Often, sci-fi movies/series can be cheesy with substandard music and dialogue, but it's easy to get caught up in and remain fascinated by this series.  What's really good is that since there so many different plots going on in the series, the intro to each episode connects what's about to be shown with what has already transpired in that plot line.  Each season continues the same high quality.
Not as good as the first three seasons
I remember this series fondly from when I was younger.  There are a few things that I really wish had been done differently now, upon re-watching it.  Such as the episode "Epiphany".
